{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 35,
  "title": "第三十五章（大象）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "執大象，天下往。"
    },
    {
      "text": "往而不害，安平大。"
    },
    {
      "text": "樂與餌，過格止。"
    },
    {
      "text": "故道之出言也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "曰：淡呵，亓無味也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "視之不足見也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "聽之不足聞也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "用之不可既也。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 9,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "萬民歸往而不傷害，則國家安寧而致太平矣。治身不害神明，則身安而大壽也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "餌，美也。過客，一也。人能樂美於道，則一留止也。一者，去盈而處虛，忽忽如過客。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 7,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道出入於口，淡淡非如五味有酸鹹苦甘辛也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 19,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "足，得也。道無形，非若五色有青黃赤白黑可得見也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 27,
          "end": 28
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道非若五音有宮商角徵羽可得聽聞也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 7,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "既，盡也。謂用道治國，則國安民昌。治身則壽命延長，無有既盡之時也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 9,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無形無識，不偏不彰，故萬物得往而不害妨也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言道之深大，人聞道之言，乃更不如樂與餌，應時感悅人心也。樂與餌則能令過客止，而道之出言淡然無味，視之不足見則不足以悅其目，聽之不足聞則不足以娛其耳，若無所中然，乃用之不可窮極也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
